From: Peter Ujfalusi <peter.ujfalusi@ti.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Oct 2013 14:32:11 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 0995/1115] ASoC: omap: Kconfig: Select Palmas clock driver if
 OMAP5 is enabled

It is common in board designs that the 32k clock is sourced from Palmas.

Signed-off-by: Peter Ujfalusi <peter.ujfalusi@ti.com>
(cherry picked from commit babfb2ca22b69f0eb905ce0cfe2925019cc4d68c)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 sound/soc/omap/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/omap/Kconfig b/sound/soc/omap/Kconfig
index eb96713..42e6180 100644
--- a/sound/soc/omap/Kconfig
+++ b/sound/soc/omap/Kconfig
@@ -92,6 +92,7 @@ config SND_OMAP_SOC_OMAP_ABE_TWL6040
 	select SND_OMAP_SOC_MCPDM
 	select SND_SOC_TWL6040
 	select SND_SOC_DMIC
+	select COMMON_CLK_PALMAS if SOC_OMAP5
 	help
 	  Say Y if you want to add support for SoC audio on OMAP boards using
 	  ABE and twl6040 codec. This driver currently supports:
